evel":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is inside queue component + persistence/config interaction. This is beyond a pure algorithm unit test if enforcement depends on persisted state and queue storage semantics. Still local DB/filesystem scope, so Integration fits and System is not strictly required. Rejected higher level: System is disqualified because no external network/subprocess/OS-only primitive is specified; local persistence integration can reproduce the failure.","test_description":"Instantiate the real persistent queue against its local storage backend with capacity N, enqueue N events successfully, then attempt N+1 and assert a capacity rejection error/state with no overflow record persisted.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.69,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
